@context: Wikipedia Comprehensive Research Marathon
@title: large_scale_navigation_and_extraction

# 🐾 WIKIPEDIA HUNT: The 50-Step Marathon

1. NAVIGATE to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page
2. VERIFY that 'Welcome to Wikipedia' is present.

3. Fill 'Search Wikipedia' field with "Pallas's cat" and press Enter
4. VERIFY that 'Otocolobus manul' is present.
5. EXTRACT the text of 'Order:' into {manul_order}
6. EXTRACT the text of 'Family:' into {manul_family}
7. Click on the 'Taxonomy' link
8. VERIFY that 'Peter Simon Pallas' is present.
9. SCROLL DOWN
10. Click on the 'Characteristics' link
11. VERIFY that 'rounded ears' is present.
12. Click on the 'Distribution and habitat' link
13. VERIFY that 'Caucasus' is present.
14. SCROLL DOWN

15. Fill 'Search Wikipedia' field with "Software testing" and press Enter
16. VERIFY that 'software quality' is present.
17. Click on the 'History' link
18. VERIFY that 'Glenford J. Myers' is present.
19. VERIFY that 'Black-box' is present.
20. SCROLL DOWN

21. Fill 'Search Wikipedia' field with "Selenium (software)" and press Enter
22. VERIFY that 'Jason Huggins' is present.
23. EXTRACT the text of 'Stable release' into {selenium_release}
24. EXTRACT the text of 'License' into {selenium_license}
25. Click on the 'Selenium WebDriver' link
26. VERIFY that 'browser automation' is present.
27. SCROLL DOWN

28. Fill 'Search Wikipedia' field with "Playwright (software)" and press Enter
29. VERIFY that 'Microsoft' is present.
30. EXTRACT the text of 'Initial release' into {playwright_release}
31. EXTRACT the text of 'Repository' into {playwright_repo}
32. Click on the 'Microsoft' link
33. VERIFY that 'Bill Gates' is present.
34. EXTRACT the text of 'Traded as' into {msft_stock}
35. EXTRACT the text of 'Headquarters' into {msft_hq}
36. Click on the 'History' link
37. VERIFY that 'Paul Allen' is present.
38. SCROLL DOWN
39. Click on the 'Corporate affairs' link
40. VERIFY that 'Board of directors' is present.

41. Fill 'Search Wikipedia' field with "Python (programming language)" and press Enter
42. VERIFY that 'Guido van Rossum' is present.
43. EXTRACT the text of 'Typing discipline' into {python_typing}
44. EXTRACT the text of 'OS' into {python_os}
45. Click on the 'Syntax and semantics' link
46. VERIFY that 'Indentation' is present.

47. Click on the 'Main menu' button
48. Click on the 'Main page' link
49. VERIFY that 'Welcome to Wikipedia' is present.
50. DONE.